Description: Fragment of oval handle from neck join to sharpish turn of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine pink-buff. Rectangular stamp with stars symbol.
Curator's comments: Ink, deleted, worn. Name Aristarchos. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, MGR P.16224?
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (57)
